modules.description: Provides functions to annotate and record execution traces of Lwt-based programs, capturing events at the thread level. Works with Lwt threads, timestamps, and custom event data to generate structured trace logs. Enables detailed analysis of asynchronous workflows in Mirage unikernels, with optional integration of additional metadata via profiling annotations.

Tracks process execution by recording timestamps and managing memory-mapped log buffers for persistent storage. Operates on bigarray structures representing raw byte buffers, enabling efficient logging to files. Used to instrument applications for performance analysis by capturing event timing data in a file-based buffer.
